can provide the receipt showing that it was properly mailed or timely received. No affidavit of an officer or employee of the claimant, or of a postal worker will be accepted as proof in lieu of the receipt. Dated: November 29, 1994. Marybeth Peters, Register of Copyrights. Approved by: James H. Billington, The Librarian of Congress. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;30045 Filed 12&hyph;6&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 1410&hyph;33&hyph;P
